LAFIA â€“ The Federal High Court sitting in Lafia on Thursday commenced the trial of Yusuf Mada, Nassarawa-Eggon West House of Assembly candidate of All Progressives Congress (APC) in the 2023 election for alleged vandalisation of rail slippers DAILY INDEPENDENT recall that the APC Assembly candidate was arraigned alongside 29 others in June 2021. Yusuf Mada was a former Special Adviser (SA) to Governor Abdullahi Sule Nasarawa State. Mada and 27 others pleaded not guilty to the allegations against them, while two of the defenders pleaded guilty. In her ruling, Justice Afolabi Nehizena the trial judge adjourned the case to November 15, 16, and 17 for the presentation of witnesses by the Prosecuting Counsel. In an interview with newsmen after the adjournment, Obafemi Tijjani, Prosecuting Counsel said those who pleaded guilty to their offences would be punishable under the act of the miscellaneous offence He assured that the police is ready to prosecute the matter to ensure that justice is served. The Prosecuting Counsel said all their witnesses are available for presentation to prove their case in the next adjourned dates.